# Security Rules

## What this file is for
Security expectations for code, configuration, and data handling.

## When to read/use this
Use when working with auth, secrets, user data, or external integrations.

## Security Principles
- Minimize sensitive data exposure.
- Validate and sanitize untrusted input.
- Follow least-privilege access patterns.

## Authentication and Authorization
- Enforce auth checks server-side.
- Keep role/permission decisions explicit and testable.

## Data Handling
- Never commit credentials or private tokens.
- Avoid logging sensitive user content.

## Common Vulnerabilities
- Guard against injection and XSS vectors.
- Ensure secure defaults for CORS and headers.
